      Typical ARGB <color/> from KML: : 7fffaaff : a1ff00ff

      * https://developers.google.com/kml/documentation/kmlreference#colorstyle * Color and opacity (alpha) values are expressed in hexadecimal notation. * The range of values for any one color is 0 to 255 (00 to ff). * For alpha, 00 is fully transparent and ff is fully opaque. * The order of expression is aabbggrr, * where aa=alpha (00 to ff); bb=blue (00 to ff); gg=green (00 to ff); rr=red (00 to ff). * For example, if you want to apply a blue color with 50 percent opacity to an overlay, you would specify the following: * <color>7fff0000</color>, where alpha=0x7f, blue=0xff, green=0x00, and red=0x00.

      Color and opacity (alpha) values are expressed in hexadecimal notation. The range of values for any one color is 0 to 255 (00 to ff). For alpha, 00 is fully transparent and ff is fully opaque. The order of expression is aabbggrr, where aa=alpha (00 to ff); bb=blue (00 to ff); gg=green (00 to ff); rr=red (00 to ff). For example, if you want to apply a blue color with 50 percent opacity to an overlay, you would specify the following: <color>7fff0000</color>, where alpha=0x7f, blue=0xff, green=0x00, and red=0x00.
